<!-- Squarespace Product Schema Suppressor v1.3 (Code-Block Safe) -->

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

          "reviewBody": "After completing the beginners course, I wasn't sure what do do next, so I signed up for some 1-2-1 sessions with Alan. This was due to Lightroom being updated recently and my Mac not being able to cope. <!-- Squarespace Product Schema Suppressor v1.3 (Code-Block Safe) -->

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

<!-- Squarespace Product Schema Suppressor v1.3 (Code-Block Safe) -->

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

          "reviewBody": "Fun, informative, and perfect for beginners.",

        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Bassam Al Jazy"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I recently attended the Landscape Photography Devon Workshop with Mr. Alan Ranger, and it was an outstanding experience from start to finish. The workshop was well-organized, with a detailed schedule and excellent information about each location — including the best times for sunrise, sunset, high tide, and low tide. Everything we needed to know was clearly explained and thoughtfully planned.  The choice of locations was perfect for training and practice. Each spot offered unique opportunities to experiment with composition, light, and timing. I must admit, I learned a lot of useful techniques, creative ideas, and ways to think differently about each shot — especially the importance of being patient and waiting for the right moment.  There were only three of us in total, which made the experience even more personal and interactive. I also learned a great deal from my fellow participants. The commuting distances between locations were short and comfortable, and Alan proved to be not only an excellent tutor but also an excellent driver!  Overall, this workshop was both educational and inspiring. I’m truly grateful for the experience and hope to join Alan again for more workshops in other locations.",

            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",

<!-- Squarespace Product Schema Suppressor v1.3 (Code-Block Safe) -->

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

<!-- Squarespace Product Schema Suppressor v1.3 (Code-Block Safe) -->

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

<!-- Squarespace Product Schema Suppressor v1.3 (Code-Block Safe) -->

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

<!-- Squarespace Product Schema Suppressor v1.3 (Code-Block Safe) -->

<script>
(function(){
  // Remove Squarespace's built-in, short Product JSON-LD
  const removeSquarespaceProduct = () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]').forEach(el => {
      const txt = el.textContent.trim();
      if (txt.includes('"@type":"Product"')) {
        try {
          const j = JSON.parse(txt);
          const looksLikeSquarespace =
            txt.length < 1500 &&
            !j.aggregateRating &&
            !j.review &&
            j.offers &&
            j.name &&
            !txt.includes('"hasMerchantReturnPolicy"');
          if (looksLikeSquarespace) el.remove();
        } catch(e){}
      }
    });
  };
  // Run several times to catch async Squarespace hydration
  removeSquarespaceProduct();
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', removeSquarespaceProduct);
  window.addEventListener('load', () => setTimeout(removeSquarespaceProduct, 1000));
  const obs = new MutationObserver(removeSquarespaceProduct);
  obs.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>

          },
          "reviewBody": "Northumbria castles and coastline! Spent a great productive and enjoyable 3 days on this workshop with Alan. Was great to be able let Alan do the driving so we could relax between venues and concentrate on taking pictures. Felt Alan got the balance slightly wrong on first day between leaving us to our own devices without being invasive and perhaps offering more advice/help but given his 5 hour drive and the fact all three of us said we had at least 20 years of experience I wasn’t too bothered. Alan was very informative and helpful on 2nd and 3rd day with technical and artistic advice. Great locations and his knowledge of the area was very helpful in achieving some really good results which he was very helpful at dinner in giving advice on. Hands on advice of camera features and technical ideas really improved my results over the 3 days combined with being able to look through Alan’s camera at his framing and his final results at the various locations.
